# Keep the Docker build context small and prevent local dev artifacts from
# shipping inside the MCP server runtime image (Dockerfile.mcp) or the
# integration-test Lambda image (Dockerfile.integ). Both Dockerfiles use
# this directory as their build context.
#
# Important rules to preserve:
# - Dockerfile.mcp does `COPY . /app` in its final stage, so anything not
#   excluded here ends up inside the runtime image.
# - Dockerfile.integ does `COPY tests/integration/`, so `tests/integration/`
#   MUST remain visible to the build. The `!tests/integration/` negation
#   below ensures unit tests are stripped while integration tests survive.
# - `conda/environment.test.yml` is intentionally NOT excluded because
#   Dockerfile.integ needs it at build time.

# --- Python bytecode and caches ---
**/__pycache__/
**/*.pyc
**/*.pyo
**/*.pyd

# --- Test / coverage / type-check caches ---
# .tox/ is the worst offender (~1.4 GB on a local dev box after running
# tox). .hypothesis/ and .pytest_cache/ are also test-runner byproducts.
**/.tox/
**/.hypothesis/
**/.pytest_cache/
**/.mypy_cache/
**/htmlcov/
**/.coverage
**/.coverage.*
.coveragerc

# --- Unit tests (integration tests are kept for Dockerfile.integ) ---
tests/
!tests/integration/
tests/integration/__pycache__/

# --- Editor / IDE / OS metadata ---
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo

# --- Version control ---
.git/
.gitignore
